WEBVTT

02:32.422 --> 02:35.046
Where is that real estate lady?

02:35.047 --> 02:38.005
She probably meant four
o'clock in the afternoon.

02:38.006 --> 02:40.005
Four o'clock in the afternoon?

02:40.006 --> 02:41.089
When does she sleep?

02:45.714 --> 02:47.756
It's what we call a fixer upper.

02:48.756 --> 02:52.046
Tell me, are we convenient
to the school here?

02:52.047 --> 02:53.921
Oh, yes, the school
is just two blocks away.

02:53.922 --> 02:57.796
And young children will
walk past here regularly?

02:57.797 --> 02:59.630
Do you two have children?

02:59.631 --> 03:00.797
As often as we can.

03:02.214 --> 03:03.214
Waldemar?

03:05.964 --> 03:07.713
Ask no more questions.

03:07.714 --> 03:11.005
We're supposed to be typical
people looking for a home.

03:11.006 --> 03:13.838
I am looking for a way into this house.

03:13.839 --> 03:17.172
You ask normal questions.

03:19.214 --> 03:21.755
Tell me, what does the building code

03:21.756 --> 03:25.296
say about filling the basement with earth?

03:25.297 --> 03:28.296
Well, um, it is a finished basement.

03:28.297 --> 03:29.338
Not yet it isn't.

03:30.547 --> 03:35.088
Oh, I do love this house.

03:35.089 --> 03:37.338
Um, there may be one small problem.

03:37.339 --> 03:38.713
It doesn't matter what it cost.

03:38.714 --> 03:39.880
Oh, it's not a matter of cost.

03:39.881 --> 03:41.880
We must get into this house.

03:41.881 --> 03:43.296
We've looked for such a long time.

03:43.297 --> 03:45.588
A very, very long time.

03:45.589 --> 03:47.796
For just this house.

03:47.797 --> 03:51.713
Well, you see, a few days ago
right after you called me...

03:51.714 --> 03:52.880
"The disposition"

03:52.881 --> 03:54.088
"of will shall be entrusted"

03:54.089 --> 03:57.171
"to my friend and attorney,
T. Armstrong Sedgeway."

03:57.172 --> 03:58.713
- Oh.
- You know,

03:58.714 --> 04:00.088
<i>I don't understand it.</i>

04:00.089 --> 04:01.588
Whenever I asked him for anything,

04:01.589 --> 04:03.171
he always said, "Leave it to me."

04:03.172 --> 04:05.546
So I figured he'd leave something to me.

04:05.547 --> 04:08.713
"And to my sister Lucille",

04:08.714 --> 04:12.338
"who could always be counted
on to borrow anything I had"

04:12.339 --> 04:14.130
"and not return it,"

04:14.131 --> 04:17.755
"I leave 3,000 overdue library books."

04:17.755 --> 04:19.546
That's all?

04:19.547 --> 04:22.671
That's all I get for being
his sister all these years?

04:26.214 --> 04:28.256
He does have one more thing for you.

04:36.172 --> 04:37.630
After what everybody else has gotten,

04:37.631 --> 04:39.338
I think we're better off he forgot us.

04:39.339 --> 04:42.921
"And to my nephew
John and his wife, Mary,

04:42.922 --> 04:46.380
"I leave my vast estate in Eerie,

04:46.381 --> 04:48.171
"Pennsylvania."
Oh.

04:48.172 --> 04:49.338
No.

04:49.339 --> 04:51.505
John, our own house.

04:51.506 --> 04:54.505
I played in that house
when I was a little boy.

04:54.506 --> 04:56.546
With all its surrounding land.

04:56.547 --> 04:58.963
We'll have a garden.

04:58.964 --> 04:59.881
Now we don't have to be afraid

04:59.882 --> 05:02.046
to let the children go out and play.

05:02.047 --> 05:03.796
That house is mine.

05:03.797 --> 05:07.296
"My attorney shall inform John and Mary"

05:07.297 --> 05:08.755
"of the curse on the house."

05:08.756 --> 05:10.130
Curse?

05:10.131 --> 05:11.755
What curse?

05:11.756 --> 05:15.506
Yes, well as I understand it...

05:20.547 --> 05:23.631
We've inherited a house with a curse.

05:24.672 --> 05:27.421
I do not
intend to lose this house.

05:27.422 --> 05:28.256
How 'bout this one?

05:28.257 --> 05:29.713
There was a young girl from Hong Kong...

05:29.714 --> 05:31.921
Billy, say goodbye
to the nice truck driver.

05:31.922 --> 05:33.046
Bye.

05:34.547 --> 05:36.713
Oh, it's wonderful.

05:36.714 --> 05:38.213
It's a wonderful house.

05:41.214 --> 05:44.463
Mary, that's not the house.

05:50.214 --> 05:51.630
This is the house?

05:51.631 --> 05:53.005
You're gonna love it here.

05:53.006 --> 05:55.088
I feel it in my bones.

05:55.089 --> 05:56.089
Come on.

06:02.006 --> 06:04.339
It's what we call a fixer upper.

06:06.006 --> 06:07.922
It's what we call home.

06:12.089 --> 06:13.630
I'm sure they won't stay very long.

06:13.631 --> 06:15.213
I'm sure they won't.

06:15.214 --> 06:16.547
<i>I know they won't.</i>

06:20.547 --> 06:22.963
Oh, it even smells
like Uncle Henry's house.

06:22.964 --> 06:25.880
It's not going to
smell like this much longer.

06:25.881 --> 06:26.714
I'll be in college before

06:26.715 --> 06:28.131
we get rid of this smell.

06:29.881 --> 06:31.214
Turn on the lights.

06:34.297 --> 06:37.714
Maybe Uncle Henry
didn't pay his electric bill.

06:39.631 --> 06:41.755
I think this place is creepy.

06:41.756 --> 06:43.963
All it needs is a little cleaning up.

06:45.672 --> 06:46.672
Where's Rover?

06:47.756 --> 06:49.463
Rover, Rover?

06:49.464 --> 06:54.422
Come on, Boy.

06:55.006 --> 06:56.006
Rover?

06:59.172 --> 07:00.921
I wonder what got into Rover?

07:00.922 --> 07:02.380
It's this place.

07:02.381 --> 07:04.088
It's creepy.

07:04.089 --> 07:06.213
Billy, why don't you go
out and bring Rover in.

07:06.214 --> 07:07.214
Billy?

07:09.006 --> 07:10.006
Billy?

07:13.547 --> 07:14.588
Billy?

07:14.589 --> 07:15.589
"Billy?"

07:17.256 --> 07:18.963
Billy?

07:18.964 --> 07:20.172
Billy?

07:22.297 --> 07:23.546
He's probably just hiding.

07:23.547 --> 07:24.381
Remember when we went

07:24.382 --> 07:27.046
to Disneyland and he hid
inside Pluto for two hours?

07:31.131 --> 07:34.297
Billy, if you're
hiding inside a big dog again...

07:35.672 --> 07:37.546
I'm not staying here alone.

08:24.631 --> 08:25.631
What?

08:26.381 --> 08:28.463
This place is so creepy.

08:28.464 --> 08:29.796
<i>Who screamed? I heard a scream.</i>

08:29.797 --> 08:31.171
Where have you been?

08:31.172 --> 08:32.506
Fixing the fuse box.

08:35.672 --> 08:36.880
You guys don't wanna send me away

08:36.881 --> 08:39.087
to boarding school or something, do you?

08:39.089 --> 08:41.087
Everything will be just fine.

08:41.089 --> 08:43.630
You'd be amazed at what some nice curtains

08:43.631 --> 08:45.089
will do to this house.

08:48.006 --> 08:49.380
I'm just worried about what this house

08:49.381 --> 08:50.421
is gonna do to me.

08:53.464 --> 08:55.256
Hey, they haven't found it yet.

08:56.339 --> 08:58.671
You can't be too sure.

08:58.672 --> 09:03.171
I, I of all people, I can't be too sure?

09:03.172 --> 09:04.714
<i>Of course, I can be sure.</i>

09:05.756 --> 09:09.963
They haven't found it
because we have to find it.

09:09.964 --> 09:11.255
It started out

09:11.256 --> 09:13.338
to be an evening just like any other,

09:13.339 --> 09:15.088
but before it was over,

09:15.089 --> 09:17.505
Millison Hackshaw would find herself in...

09:17.506 --> 09:19.963
Was an innocent teenage girl.

09:19.964 --> 09:22.505
She had no idea that the terrible events

09:22.506 --> 09:23.630
building around her would plunge her...

09:23.631 --> 09:26.088
Is that what you call looking at the TV?

09:26.089 --> 09:27.796
I've tried every channel and all I get

09:27.797 --> 09:29.755
is The Twilight Zone.
Her father opened the door

09:29.756 --> 09:31.505
and stepped out...
Lightning always

09:31.506 --> 09:32.921
does that to the TV reception.

09:33.922 --> 09:34.839
A dimension of sight

09:34.840 --> 09:37.088
and sound and smell.

09:37.089 --> 09:38.588
A dimension of Oriental...

09:38.589 --> 09:40.130
It'll be alright once the storm is over.

09:40.131 --> 09:42.505
A dimension
of abandoned lumberyards.

09:42.506 --> 09:44.296
A dimension of railway stations

09:44.297 --> 09:48.796
that have stopped being grand
and are nowhere near central.

09:48.797 --> 09:51.338
There's a train leaving from that station,

09:51.339 --> 09:55.671
and it's destination is Cincinnati, Ohio.

10:01.547 --> 10:02.547
What storm?

10:24.797 --> 10:25.797
